Package: mali-valhall-g610-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Rockchip Mali-Valhall (CSF) GPU kernel driver (valhall_kbase, DKMS)
 Builds valhall_kbase.ko, the ARM Mali-Valhall "kbase" kernel module for the
 Mali-G610 (CSF) GPU on Rockchip RK3588 (platform "rk", ARM DDK g29p1). The
 rk35xx 6.1 vendor driver is ported to build and run on mainline ARM64 kernels
 (developed against 7.1.2-edge-rockchip64); it drives /dev/mali0 for the
 proprietary libmali userspace, displacing the in-tree panthor driver.
 .
 DKMS rebuilds the module for each installed kernel that has the matching
 linux-headers package present.
 .
 Under /usr/src/mali-valhall-g610-g29p1/kernel-patches/ the package also ships
 the kernel patches the libmali + Zink + XWayland userspace needs once panthor
 is displaced -- a rockchip-drm render node and the system-uncached dma-heap --
 plus an optional GPU page-migration patch. Those patch the kernel itself and
 are therefore NOT applied by DKMS; see README.md for how to apply them.
